The integration of IEEE 802.1 Time-sensitive Networking (TSN) with wireless technologies promises to support realtime applications over hybrid networks. Although TSN over Ethernet is well established, extending its capabilities to WiFi remains a technical challenge due to hardware and protocol differences. In this work, we integrate a core TSN scheduling mechanism, IEEE 802.1Qbv Time-aware Shaper (TAS), with WiFi interfaces in the Linux kernel. Our approach enables scheduling for mixed-criticality traffic over wired and wireless links using standard Linux tools. We provide our implementation and evaluation scenarios as open source to support further research in TSN-WiFi integration.